<methods><methodStep><description><section><title>Crosshair Classification</title>
<para>Crosshair classification tests the null hypothesis that populations are &quot;exchangeable&quot;, in each of four ways: recent genetic, recent ecological, historical genetic, historical ecological. In the data table, the R stands for &quot;rejected&quot; (i.e. null hypothesis rejected, suggesting that the populations are distinct) and NR stands for &quot;not rejected&quot; (populations are not distinct).</para>
</section>
